That was totally not me for the first year of owning FL...I went from the "Tools" method for a year, to noticing with FL native plug-ins I can just right-click any knob. 3:12 PM
But the way FL works is very efficient and unique compared to many other DAWs, everything is a choice, assignable, I pick if and what channel strip I want my sound to go to, and where in the playlist I want my patterns/tracks. Logic is powerful and comes with hundreds of thousands of built in things, but once you have a track, it assigns itself to its matching numbered channel strip, and it's matching numbered track in the playlist.
